  "prompt": "What is kale called in Hindi or Marathi?",
  "response": "Kale is commonly referred to as \"kale\" in both Hindi and Marathi, as it is not a traditional vegetable in India and often retains its English name. However, some might refer to it as \"\u0939\u0930\u0940 \u092a\u0924\u094d\u0924\u093e\u0917\u094b\u092d\u0940\" (Hari Pattagobhi) in Hindi or \"\u0939\u093f\u0930\u0935\u0940 \u092a\u093e\u0932\u0947\u092d\u093e\u091c\u0940\" (Hirvi Palebhaji) in Marathi, which generally means green leafy vegetable.",
